# Wire Dependency Injection Standards

The project uses Google Wire for compile-time dependency injection, configured in `internal/di/wire.go`.

## Current Provider Organization

```go
//go:build wireinject

package di

import (
    delivery "go-clean-arch/internal/shared/adapter/delivery"
    userHandler "go-clean-arch/internal/user/adapter/delivery/http/handler"
    userRepo "go-clean-arch/internal/user/adapter/repository"
    userUsecase "go-clean-arch/internal/user/usecase"
    "go-clean-arch/pkg/auth"
    "go-clean-arch/pkg/config"
    "go-clean-arch/pkg/db"

    "github.com/google/wire"
)

func InitializeAPI(cfg config.Config) (*delivery.Server, error) {
    wire.Build(
        db.ConnectDatabase,
        auth.NewTokenService,
        userRepo.NewUserRepository,
        wire.Bind(new(userUsecase.UserRepository), new(*userRepo.UserRepository)),
        userUsecase.NewUserManager,
        userHandler.NewUserHandler,
        delivery.NewServer,
    )
    return &delivery.Server{}, nil
}
```

## Interface Binding

```go
// Bind concrete implementation to the interface defined in the usecase layer
wire.Bind(new(userUsecase.UserRepository), new(*userRepo.UserRepository))
```

## Adding a New Domain Module

### 1. Add new Repository

```go
articleRepo.NewArticleRepository,
wire.Bind(new(articleUsecase.ArticleRepository), new(*articleRepo.ArticleRepository)),
```

### 2. Add new Manager

```go
articleUsecase.NewArticleManager,
```

### 3. Add new Handler

```go
articleHandler.NewArticleHandler,
```

### 4. Update Server constructor

`NewServer` must accept the new Handler parameter:

```go
func NewServer(
    userHandler *userHandler.UserHandler,
    articleHandler *articleHandler.ArticleHandler,
) *Server {
    // ...
    router.SetupRouter(engine, router.RouterParams{
        UserHandler:    userHandler,
        ArticleHandler: articleHandler,
    })
    // ...
}
```

## Import Alias Conventions

When multiple domains have packages with the same name, use aliases:

```go
import (
    userHandler "go-clean-arch/internal/user/adapter/delivery/http/handler"
    userRepo "go-clean-arch/internal/user/adapter/repository"
    userUsecase "go-clean-arch/internal/user/usecase"

    articleHandler "go-clean-arch/internal/article/adapter/delivery/http/handler"
    articleRepo "go-clean-arch/internal/article/adapter/repository"
    articleUsecase "go-clean-arch/internal/article/usecase"
)
```

## Code Generation

After modifying `wire.go`, run:

```bash
make di
```

This generates the `wire_gen.go` file.

